# Licensing

This project uses a split license model:

## Source Code — MIT License

All source code (everything except the `tools/` directory) is licensed under the MIT License.

See [LICENSE-CODE](LICENSE-CODE) for full terms.

**Summary:** You can freely use, modify, and distribute the code for any purpose, including commercial use.

## Tool Catalog — Creative Commons BY-NC-SA 4.0

The curated AI tool catalog in the `tools/` directory is licensed under Creative Commons Attribution-NonCommercial-ShareAlike 4.0 International.

See [LICENSE-CATALOG](LICENSE-CATALOG) for full terms.

**Summary:** You can freely share and adapt the catalog content, but:
- ✅ **Attribution required** — Credit Agentic AI For Good
- ❌ **No commercial use** — Can't sell the catalog or use in commercial products without permission
- 🔄 **ShareAlike** — Derivatives must use the same license

## Why Split Licensing?

**Code is MIT** so developers can build on this codebase freely — fork it, modify it, use it commercially.

**Catalog is CC BY-NC-SA** to protect the hundreds of hours of curation work from being copied wholesale into commercial products. If you want to use the catalog commercially, please contact us.

## What This Means For:

### 🛠️ Developers building tools
- ✅ Fork the code, customize it, deploy your own version (MIT)
- ✅ Use the catalog for personal projects or open source tools (CC BY-NC-SA)
- ❌ Package the catalog into a paid product without permission

### 📚 Researchers & educators
- ✅ Use both code and catalog freely for non-commercial research/education
- ✅ Cite this project in papers or educational materials

### 🏢 Companies
- ✅ Use the codebase as a template for internal tools (MIT)
- ❌ Cannot resell or embed the catalog in commercial products
- 💬 Contact us for commercial licensing: hello@agenticaiforgood.com

### 🤝 Contributors
By contributing to this project, you agree that:
- Code contributions are licensed under MIT
- Catalog contributions (`tools/*.yaml`) are licensed under CC BY-NC-SA 4.0

